author: SportTheFoole
body:
Repealing 230 would be a disaster. Tech will take a huge shit (and presumably pull down the rest of the market with it). 

Here’s what 230 (the bit in the CDA extends a 1936 telecommunications law to the internet) says: if you run a website with content from a third party, then you can’t be held legally liable for the content posted by that third party. Basically Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, etc could not exist without these protections. (IIRC, and some should probably fact check me on this, the original 230 was basically that you can’t sue Ma Bell because some jackhole calls you on the phone to call you a motherfucker). 

Disclaimer: I am not a lawyer, this is what I’ve gleamed from law Twitter.
